<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
i3ullseye<P>If I had it to do over again, I'd still take a theurgist over a sorc.  However, if I wanted to do crowd control, I'd move to midgard and take a healer.  I like my current guild, and I'm not going to get 37 levels again, so I'm stuck playing the sorcerer.   I still like the concept underlying a sorceror, but my RVR crowd-control abilities are a pale shadow of what a healer can do, and they get healing abilities on top of them. As long as that's true, regardess of the NUMBER of tools I have, I am NOT the premier crowd control class, at least in rvr which is what matters to me.  <P>And the NUMBER of people saying this does not change this fact...it is true regardless of how many people post or don't post on it.  Yeah, I've had some successes with mez, and I've even managed to get a pet in rvr and use it once in awhile.  I'd still take the dwarf healer.  <P>To add insult to injury, I made it to the top of a keep last night and wanted to help kill the realm lord.  Turns out he was IMMUNE to all the spells I cast on him.  DD, debuffs, DOT, even amnesia.  Know any Mobs immune to melee?<P>I already can't affect the gates of the keep, and now I can't even affect the realm lord.  Maybe I could sick a pet on him, but for that I'd actually need to get a pet and not die 5 times getting to the lord.  Pet-using classes with armor MIGHT be able to do that, and on a very good day, I might too, but most days I'm going to die at least once getting into the keep and then the pet is gone.  <P>Shrug.  Ya other classes have problems too, and mythic is no doubt frantically trying to address all of them.  K, I can understand that and I can even be patient.  <P>What would help most is communication.  Are there any plans to fix the sorc in rvr or is the rvr weakness a done deal?  Just knowing the answer to that question without specifics would make a big difference as to how I view my sorc.  <P>Secondly, what suggestions are you currently putting forth to the devs for fixing rvr?  Knowing that would also be a big help, along with what your guess as to the chances the suggestion will get implemented at some point.<P>If our posts here are going to fall on deaf ears because we are a minority, I'll happily stop posting.  If, however, you think these posts have some value, I'll attempt to keep contributing.  Up to you, just let me know.  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>Tequitus
