<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I have to disagree with our cleric friend about grouping with Sorc.<P>But it does point ot a trend I've been seeing starting in the Catacombs and continuing to the Barrows.<P>This is the 5 tank, 3 healer grp.<P>Yep, no room for "non-essentials" such as scouts, Inf. Wiz, Sorc etc.<P>Its the melee xp game brought to its natural conclusion.  It also points to more of an EQ ( me first) attitude that is pervasive still.<P>Some players seem to forget that ALL classes are needed and should be welcome to a party and not the minimum most xp effective set.<P>An argument for Diversity!<P>Players playing too close to the vest will wonder where the AE attack of the Wizard is when they are confronted with a mob of trolls.  Players will bemoan the lack of any high level stealth players.<P>I suspect that many have not made the RVR transition mindset and are still playing in a PVE game that they are familiar with.<P>Dyyphyz
