I have to strongly disagree that making the speed spell a single target cast buff would be the best thing.  I don't know about the rest of you, but I despise having to constantly recast buffs for myself and group members.<P>The very reason that I quit playing a high level theurgist was because I could not stand their role in groups, all I was doing was casting speed buff, damage add buff and bladeturn.  Sure theurgists can solo like the Wind (pun intended) and have a nice array of spells, but constantly being a buff vending machine is not my idea of a fun game.<P>Frankly I love the idea of concentration based spells and group chant spells that do not require active renewal on my part.  If the speed spell were turned into a single target castable CONCENTRATION based buff then I would agree it would be a wonderful thing, but not as a buff that constantly requires me to replenish it.  Just put a quarter slot on me and i'll vend soft drinks as well...<P>From my point of view: Leave the speed spell as an area range chant type spell but have it affect our pets.  This will maximize my happiness on this issue, I do not play to be a vending machine.<P>--------------------<P>Rinh the Sorceress<BR>Guinevere
