Wow, do you read what i post?<P>i KNOW the mez duration is the biggest issue. i have been trying to get some support to repeal the change since it went onto test. And yes there IS a focus gorup avaialble on Pendragon, it's called log in and play there. that is all us team leads really are, a central voice for testing gorups on Pendragon. So your idea is great, now jump on over to Pendragon and back it up!<P>Here is reality for you.<P>Again i did state level 50 with full specs. So now we will focus on JUSt a single line versus a single line.<P>Say we go pure mind versus pure smite.<BR>&*&*&*&*&*&*&**&*&**&*&*&*&*&*&*&<P>Smite gets a 225 DD, and a 153 AE DD. But the net result is doing 225 on a single cast maximum, no matetr how you slice it, since you can not cast more than one spell a round in reality.<P>Our damage is STILL a 141 DD, and a 316 total DOT. Break the DOT out and you will see we can do a direct amount of 220 per round (141 Dd plus the 79 dot) pretty damn close and this is in out BASE line of body and matter. no spec needed.<P>Now add the Mind spec and our Mez duration is over double the clerics, and is AE. <P>this is also the spec path that gets the nice CON debuff which can factor into this, but we will ignore it as the numbers themselves speak volumes.<P><BR>*&*&*&*&**&*&*&*&**&*&**&**&*&<P>not enough?<P>Single smite versus single body.<P>&*&*&*&***&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&**&**<BR>Now the clerics smite does not change. he is a suck ass healer because all he does is smite and CC. What does the sorceror do?<P>Now we have a 210 DD, that adds to the 316 DOT. This gives us a 289 damage per round if we break it out. Our single target mez is STILL over double theirs, and now we have a decent snare spell also, which they do not get.<BR>*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&**&*&*&**&*&*&*<P>Still not happy? Lets assume some sadistic bastard full specs matter, which by all opinions here seems to be gimped beyond playability.<P>*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*<BR>Again our sucky, non healing, no buffing cleric is still going to have the same numbers.<P>What about the sorceror?<P>Now it is a 534 point DOT, with the 141 dd. Spreading that it lasts 6 turns instead of 4, and can do 230 per round. Also add in the AE Snare in that matter line.<P>And hey, guess what? OUR MEZ IS STILL DOUBLE A CLERICS!<BR>*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&*&&*&*&<P>So I don't know where my real world is flawed, but it all seems pretty clear to me. the numbers are there. The spells are there to use. There are quite a few sorcerors in the 40's across the servers compared to many other classes, and you don;t get there by being completely useless.<P>There are problems, but if your going to compare us to another class come with facts. If your goingg to blast me, at least be close to accurrate.  ANY of the 3 spec paths of a sorceror has better CC potential than a Cleric (i did not even mention confusion or amnesia, let alone a pet). ANY spec path of sorceror out-damages a cleric (Again leaving out all melee concerns, because our pet WILL take an even level cleric easy).<P>So please, someone if your going to get all worked up about this post soemthing to substantiate the claims. here, i will go over my list YET AGAIN....<P><BR>1) mez duration was a bad change, it hurts us and needs to be put back.<P>2) Speed spell need to work on pets (this is to be fixed soon).<P>3) We need more charmable humanoids (also to be remedied soon).<P>4) Amnesia is broken (will be fixed).<P>5) Matter line needs more to it (spells will be added here).<P><BR>And that is about it. We need to FIX things before we can move on. We are NOT broken in many areas that people just seem to be unhappy with. <P>Prove we are broken across the board.<P>Prove that a Cleric or minstrel or theurgist is superior in crowd control ACROSS THE BOARD.<P>Otherwise it just may be a case of them playing their class well and creatively, and the sorceror in question having no clue how to use the tools at their disposal.<P>--------------------<P>i3ullseye<BR>"You're good, but me? I'm Magic!"<P>Rictus -Sorceror(DAOC)/Rictus(EQ)<BR>DAOC Sorceror team lead...
