<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I give up, Bullshit, your incredible cut and paste skills are too much for me.<P>Comparing DoT damage to DD: misleading.  Doesn't factor in time, nor resist rates for the vast majority of non-Matter sorcs.  Nor power costs, which are huge.<P>Saying a Cleric cannot cast a Smite and a Shout in the same round: incorrect.  Every 20 seconds (NOT minutes, as you would know if you didn't get your stuff from books) a Smite Cleric can Shout (insta-cast) an AE DD.<P>Saying a full spec Smite Cleric is a poor healer:  Only in relation to full Rejuv Clerics!  They get two heals in their base Rejuv line, at 50th they can heal for 231.  That ain't shabby for the damage and cc they can dish out.<P>Further, when we compare in CC, let's consider other factors, such as worst case scenarios.  If a Cleric is resisted with his AE Mez, he can actually take some hits (Chain vs. Cloth, Cleric HP vs. Caster HP) before being in trouble.  He can insta-heal himself, if he's bothered to put 11 points into Rejuv (and most Smite clerics do at least that).  He also has the AF and HP to last long enough for a SECOND healer to heal him, or for a tank to disengage from the first mob and smack the one on the cleric.  They have several options.<P>If WE are resisted, we have much fewer options.  Quickcast mez again, and pray.  We don't get much time for other options; we die too quickly.  Factor in the lovely mob behavior that allows them to smack us from across the room when ANOTHER PERSON breaks our mez, and we are usually the first to die, and the most often to die.<P>Lastly, regarding Mez duration:  That's a joke, right?  How long does it take 2-3 tanks to beat down a red or low purple mob?  If they have any kind of nuke support, I'd estimate 4-7 seconds.  Call it 10 seconds if you factor moving from one mezzed mob to the next.  Also factor in the 3 seconds it takes us to cast mez, vs. insta-mez.  In 3 seconds, a Megalith Wight can come from the next room and be on your ass.  More like 1.5 seconds.  The Cleric just stands in the doorway and Shouts.<P>So the Cleric not only can Shout AE Mez instantly, thereby keeping the mobs further from the casters and other clerics, and bunched together, but can survive much better if resisted.  Further, in most of the places 30+ groups hunt, undead is the rule, not the exception.  So not only do they out DD us on the baseline, but they receive the highest bonuses possible ABOVE the base damage.<P>I'm not going to fulfill your narrow requirements in an argument; I'm going to look at the whole picture.  Clerics can handle CC better than Sorcs.  Across the board.<P>--------------------<P><B>Baelzar<BR>41st Level Sorceror<BR>Redemption<BR>Iseult/Albion</B>
</FONT>
