I think when they say a cleric can do CC better it should be noted, most instances they're using is IF there are 2 clerics...then the Smiter takes CC, and backup healer while the other is Primary healer. I play a cleric as my primary and That's the only time I'll play as crowd control. But in that instance I usaly CAN survive better than a sorcerer Unless he's almost toatly mind spec and dosn't have to worry about resists.<P>Edit: Btw, I pretty much have a balanced cleric (14 rejuv 14 enhance and 9 smite)So if I'm with another cleric who's a spec heavily in Rejuv I will do crowd control, but not if I'm by myself.<P>--------------------<P>Albion Bedvedere Server:<BR>Jerid DeGray Lev 23 Cleric-500 Armorcrafter<BR>Nevyl Mindweaver Lev 17 Sorcerer- 510 Tailor<BR>Garvin Brightshield Lev 14 Paladin-360 Weaponcrafter<P>Solari Earthsinger Lev 12 Theurgist-0 Spellcrafter <P>"It's not a dress damnit! It's a Fine Manly Robe!!"
