<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Alright i3ullseye, I've been reading this board for almost as long as when this game went live.  I used to think i3ullseye as someone who has some unique experience and strategies as a beta tester and TL, but your recent posts do NOT make much sense most of the time and you are becoming very defensive and therefore not thinking clearly (or just lack the knowledge).  <BR>-------------------------------------------<BR>On your statments about theugs, there is no denying they are the single best solo class.  Just the other day guildie told me, oh gee, did Mythic nerf my pets?  It used to take me 5 pets to solo an orange, now I need 7?  how outrageous.  Theugs have solo'ing down to exact science.  they know how many pets they need for yellows, orange, and reds.<BR>-------------------------------------------<BR>From your posts about theugs and smiter clerics, it shows you have no experience interacting with them nor have you talk to any real life person.  I've recently decided to put off my Sorc and make a smiter cleric, so I've talked to a few of my smiter friends.<P>Fact:<BR>At lvl 37, a fully spec'ed smiter with items (and some points in rejuv and enhance) can do good 300 a pop on undeads with 3sec base smite.  Further, with Yog's mace, he can swing for about 30 + about 40 added dmg from his dmg buff.  He has almost 1000hp buffed and chain armor, so he can easily melee and tank if he had to.  And this is on reds and light purples.<P>Fact:  <BR>At lvl 41, with 2/3 spec in body, I can nuke 120-150 with lvl 22 body spec nuke, and 140-180 with base.  Having no points in matter cept for items, my DOT does anywhere from 50-80.  This is also on reds and light purples.<P>I'll let you draw your own conclusions on that one.  And btw i3ullseye when you say "fully spec in mind" that means you have 0 points in matter and 0 points in body, so your DD variation is going to vary so much it's not funny.  Even with fully spec in body or in matter, one of the other line's dmg output isn't going to be pretty either.<P>That's just some fyi info. clerics can easily out dmg us, oh well, I can take that, since we have other perks, can't compare fairly.  <BR>-------------------------------------------<BR>As for CC, I would say each class have their strength and weakness.  Let me paint the scenario.  In barrows, wights/celts room.  This is the most challenging place for CC in my career so far, when pulls can easily go 3+, no room to run or work with, tight corridors so have to watch AE, and possible ADD with bad luck.<P>Smiter have stuns and insta AE Mez, and a tough body to withstand hits.  This is plenty enough to do groups of 3 red/light purp pulls.  When there is the hairy 6+ pulls, clerics and be somewhat lacking, but due to stuns and smites to take a mob down fast, still very much doable. (stun means dont need as much healing)<P>Theugs:  You wouldn't think they CC very well or even can at all, and really I've only seen one that actually does it, but he was quite good at what he was doing.  With his AE mez and AE/single root depending how they spend points, he can easily CC 3 pulls.  on 6+, they can send out pets and still get the job done.  Tough, but still doable.<P>Minstrels: insta stun, single mez.  You would think minstrels can't CC all that well, but your are wrong.  They handle 3 pulls with ease, since fights dont last that long anyways, and they have nothing better to do.  On 6+ pulls, they might have a bit of trouble due to lack of AE.  But they can still get the job done.  I've seen a minstrel kept a mob busy for about 2 minutes.  Constantly mezzing, the mob sometimes would slip out of mez and get off an attack, but would be lulled back to sleep. They also have confuse as a emergency tool.<BR>  <BR>Now, as for my sorc, the minute long mezzes doesn't really mean much.  It just means I only need to cast one AE mez during begining of fight.  Only time I need to remez is on the 6+ pulls.  *shrug*  Yes I do have Amenesia and confuse, but seriously how often do I use those?  Pets for CC is pretty nice, but how often would I keep a pet if I'm in a group?  Assuming when they bother to fix the speed spell, I still would not spend the time to fetch a pet because pathing and zoning issue, assuming good enough pets are even close enough to charm.<P>To summarize, for serious CC (6+ pulls with possible add), Sorc is still ultimate in the sense that assuming not much resist, we can keep chaos to minimum, with minstrel close behind.  But for your everyday 3-4 pulls, minstrels, smiters, and theugs can do just as well if not better.<BR>Is there something wrong with that picture?  You can argue it both ways.  But the problem I see is what ELSE the other classes can bring.<BR>Theugs: possiblilities are: pulsing Bladeturn, attack buffs (speed and dmg).<BR>Minstrel: Power song. (what more do you need =p )<BR>Smiters:  Base buff and backup healing.  And fyi, I tend to find smiters better healers, or atleast keep group alive better than higher lvl rejuv clerics.  Maybe they are more stingy with their healing...or just stuns alone is good enough to keep healing minimum.  I lived through a 7 pull wights with 1 single cleric of lvl 35, I was 38 and tanks are 37-40 ish and 1 pally who was doing armor chant.  Afterwards I was praising the cleric for keeping calm and getting us through the madness. The cleric told us then he was a smiter cleric.<P>Sorcs:  2-3 debuffs (I dont have dex debuff) which, most of the time, is useless.  Why?  The resists are horrible, on red and purps I try to lend the 2 spec debuffs in, and by the time they stick, I usually decide NOT to use DOT since I'll prolly only get 2 ticks out of it.  Also, in dungeons or just some closer pulls, AE spells means breaking mez, or worse, aggroing mobs nearby = insta death.  And even after landing the debuffs, the effects aren't so easily detectable. So what's left, my nuke and DOT?  My DOT (due to no points in it) cost horrible amount of power, and gets resisted good half the time which means even more horrible waste of power.  And unless I manage to land it early, it's so not worth the power.  My nuke? 120 ish nukes is about 1 swipe from a halby tank, not using style.  Boy do I feel useful.  <BR>(and just another interesting FYI.  One day I was running towards Sauvage for some RvR and saw some newbie got in trouble due to ADDs.  So instead of just killing the adds off I decided to debuff them all with my 2 spec debuffs, thinking they wont even be able to tough the newbie even if they land any hits.  To my horror, the newbie died after killing the 2nd mob as the 3rd one beat on me.  I felt sooooo bad.  If I was a theug or cleric I could have buffed him and I bet he could have finished the adds all off.  What's wrong with the debuffs?????  This was lvl 5 newbie, am I too high to debuff newbie mobs??  Or is there a limit to how much you can debuff a mob?  Or is a mob capable of dishing out damage having -str, -con, -dex and -quick?  I just dont understand)<P>Anyways all this I've experienced with personally.  (so I spend a lot of time in barrows, sue me) These aren't just number crunching "facts" based off the strategy guides or some sites, this is based on real situations.  <BR>--------------------------------------------<BR>Another point to make: Even if all the "minority" of sorcs on this board move over to pendragon, guess what?  We still would not be able to test things well enough.  Not enough grouping experience, no enough ppl to RvR with, hard to find regulars to group with.  And some things can't be tested even with a single fully populated server.  <BR>-----------------------------------------<BR>For single cast speed buffs:  I agree with most other ppl.  I dont want to be EQ druid (SOW) nor clerics (rez) being bombarded with ppl asking me for buff.  Now, if they made it conc based or if this buff works during battle, I would be willing.  But I dont see any of that happening, so pls dont make me a vending machine.  <BR>------------------------------------------<BR>Amnesia:  You stated that supposively new amnesia would TOTALLY wipe out a monster's aggro list.  This would mean the exp of the monster would be reset.  This means you can fight a mob till you need to stop, cast amnesia (assuming you can somehow get far enough away so monster wont reaggro) and med until you are ready to finish it off.  Means you can twink your friends, or get twinked, by others who can do most of the damage for you.  Dont see this happening.<BR>Also, unless you are fighting neutrals, amnesia should also have a few secs of stuns allowing ppl to get away.  Or the mob has to somehow walk away by itself for a short period of time, otherwise the "total wiping of aggro list" would have 0 difference with how it's currently implemented. ie mob just goes to knock out whoever is right next to it, which is prolly some poor caster, or worse, yourself.<BR>--------------------------------------------<BR>Mez duration:  I have not experienced too many instances of the nerf, ever since lvl 37 (might have been 38)  BUT, when it DOES happen, it means instant death for me and possibly other members of the group.  My groups depend on my mez.  When I can't reliably mez and tell them when it's about to break, I'm a sad sorc and ppl wouldn't want to group with me or bother with multi pulls.  What happens sometimes is mez will break after 5 secs or less.  Very strange, and REALLY pisses me off.  <BR>Here's the scenario: We are at the mage room in barrows, just below the advisor room.  Puller pulls, usually 3 aggros per pull.  1 comes to the group since puller keep shooting, while other mobs sits back and cast.  I mez the other 2 have the puller bring them in 1 at time as the group is ready.  Very typical setup.  First night, things went pretty well, only a few deaths through the night once we figured out that as long as the clerics can buff casters above 620hp, we'll live through any single nuke.  Many times I'll be at a sliver of hp but I'll live to laugh in the face of the mages.  Second night, I brought in a different group but all of them are 1-3 lvls higher than previous nights.  And these guys are my guildies, they know how to work with me.  We camped there for an hour, and had 2 group wipe outs along with other deaths.  Why?  My mez was having hiccups.  They would break at random times, usually lasting for 5 secs or less.  I know my mez stuck. How could I tell?  Because the mage was in middle of casting a nuke, then he dropped his hands and stood there.  5 secs later, a nuke pops right out of its hand and BAM cleric (who is sitting on top of the stairs healing)is almost dead.  Since only a couple of the tanks even had range attacks, and it was easy to see that they were all busy whacking on the mob that was pulled, it was easy to tell that no one broke my mez.  The mezzed mobs were also quite far away, being casters and all, so there was no chance that an area spell or swipe could have accidently broke mez.  We ended up doing advisors upstairs. Even though advisors are only about 2 lvls higher than mages and have no group bonus, they ended up being better exp since there was no downtime and no danger, even though spawn could be slow at time and I was bored out of my mind doing my mediocre DOT and sad nukes.  <BR>If you ask me how do I think about the mez nerf, my answer to you NOW would be:  it seems okay, dont feel much, just loving bladeturn is all.  Why? because I dare to guess most 40+ sorcs are fighting stuff that's orange and red, there just isn't that many mobs that's still purple and comes in 2+.  There isn't anymore good spots that gropus can do 1 single tough purple, or even tough red and purp multi pulls.  80% of the 40+ on my server got their post 40 exp from barrows from constant pulling groups of orange/red mobs and relying on group exp.  That being said, the few times we pulled liches which still cons high red and light purp still, I swear I still get funky mez times, but usually my group ignored my mez and just whacked/smited the liches in fear of their insta 700+ nuke, so really dont have chance to test and tell you more about mez nerf.  But the nights at mage room have left deep gashes in my brains, I will never be able to trust my mez fully anymore.  I had to say to my guildies "sorry guys, I guess I can't trust my mez anymore, we should prolly move somewhere else" after I dragged them to barrows and told them how easy it would be.<BR>-------------------------------------------<BR>Now, PvE, well, things aren't nice for us, but through doing crappier mobs I'm still lvling so oh well.  (even lvl 46 ppl are still doing celts/wights which cons yellow/orange)  But as for RvR, I feel fairly useless.<BR>Yes I have the 2nd most feared spell, AE mez.  Now that I have 2k+ rp, and having done rvr for a couple weeks now, I think we need some serious help.  <BR>The only 2 things I offer during rvr is mez and speed buff.  But rarely can I get off a mez due to lag/stunGard since our range and casting time is pretty sorry.  When I DO get an AE off, usually I get nuked to death afterwards by casters who stood back far enough to elude my area.  The few times when I caught a group by surprise, I managed to find ranger types and DOT/nuked them to death (hoping they had less hp) but wow it takes a lot of nukes to bring an even con down.  So besides the occasional mez that I can get out and run buff, I really have very little to offer in RvR.  I could go through how useful the other 3 classes are in RvR, but I dont think you need me to explain.  Sufficice to say insta mez + stun, super run + stealth + power song, and theug can solo well and bolt cast pets, pulse BB, buffs, mez... sigh.  I would use debuff but then if I had time for that I would cast mez, and after that I can't debuff anymore...heh.<P>Anyways, that pretty much sums up life as lvl 40 sorc, and some comparisons with other classes, as well as my views on some of the issues.  Sorry this is so long but I've kept silent for far too long and watching i3ullseye becoming less rational with each post I've finally took the time to speak out.<BR>I dont think by going to Pendragon things will work out and we'll be heard etc.  No incentive for ppl to be testing things there and as I said some issues isn't going to be discovered on 1 server alone.  This board is a great place for sorc discussions, we just need to let the whole sorc community across the servers know about this board so this is no longer a "vocal minority" of sorcs.<BR>Anyways, after playing my friend's pally for a few days, I think it's time to dust off my sorc and go explore Lyoness...and then it's off to roll a smiter cleric until they make being a sorcess fun again.<P>--------------------<P>Sephrenia Fairheart<BR>41.5 Sorceress of Guinevere<BR>41(34)mind/0(5)matter/24(28)body
