<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Ok, here is a damage comparison including the modifier from spec.  The specialization formula used to determine effectiveness is<P>  ((your spec level / your lvl) + 1.25) / 2<P>So full spec damage multiplier is 1.125  :  ((50/50)) + 1.25) / 2<BR>Unspecced damage multiplier is  .635 :  ((1/50)) + 1.25) / 2<P>These multipliers calculate average damage.  Lets look at two cases, one where the fight lasts 10 seconds (a normal group fight) and another where a fight lasts 20 seconds (unusually long fight).  I think that the spell information truncates the casting time, because smite is listed as 3 seconds when it is actually closer to 4.  Lifetap spells are listed as 2 seconds, but they are really 2.5?  I will assume they are 2.5 for this.<P><BR>Full Smite<P>Smite does 225 * 1.125 = 253<P><BR>10 sec fight:<BR>Cleric can cast 2 smites so 281 + 281 = 562<BR>Against undead 562 * 1.25 = 703<BR>20 sec fight:<BR>Cleric can cast 4 smites so 281 * 4 = 1124<BR>Against undead 1124 * 1.25 = 1406<P><BR>Full Mind<P>Life Drain does 141 * .635 = 90<BR>Disintegrating Smoke does 79 * .635= 50 per tick (every 5 seconds)<P>10 sec fight:<BR>Sorcerer casting smoke first and  2 lifedrain after would get 2 ticks of smoke and two lifedrains so they would do 50+50+90+90 = 280<BR>20 sec fight:<BR>Sorcerer casting smoke first and  2 lifedrain after would get 4 ticks of smoke and six lifedrains so they would do 50*4 + 6*90 = 760<P>Full Body<P>Mind Flay does 210 * 1.125 = 236<BR>Disintegrating Smoke does 79 = 50 per tick (every 5 seconds)<P>10 sec fight:<BR>Sorcerer casts Lifedrain three times so it would do 236 * 3 = 708<BR>20 sec fight:<BR>Sorcerer casts Lifedrain seven times so it would do 236 * 7 = 1652<P><BR>Full Matter<P>Life Drain does 141 * .635 = 90<BR>Disintegrating Force 89 * 1.125 = 100 (every 4 seconds)<P>10 second fight:<BR>Sorcerer casting Force first and lifedrain after would get 2 ticks of force and two lifedrains so they would do 100 * 2 + 90 * 2 = 380<BR>20 second fight:<BR>Sorcerer casting Force first and lifedrain after would get 5 ticks of force and six lifedrains so they would do 100*5 + 90*6  1060<P>All numbers below represent damage done assuming no resists and equal con enemies. <P>Summery for 10 second fight:<P>Smite Cleric: 562<BR>SC against Undead: 703<BR>Mind Sorcerer: 280<BR>Body Sorcerer: 708<BR>Matter Sorcerer: 380<P>Summery for 20 second fight:<P>Smite Cleric: 1124<BR>SC against Undead: 1406<BR>Mind Sorcerer: 760<BR>Body Sorcerer: 1652<BR>Matter Sorcerer: 1060<P><BR>Assuming cast times are correct, it looks like that Body Sorcerer blows away any other sorcerer or smite cleric when it comes to damage.  Smite Cleric comes in at a strong second and equal body in a short fight.  Matter Sorcerer comes in third and almost catchs up with smite cleric in a long fight where the DoT gets a chance to work, even though that is rare.  Fourth comes Mind spec, who is severely gimped in damage but makes up for it in theory by having better CC.  Fights rarely if ever last 20 seconds, but I wanted to see if DoT's help out in damage for longer fights and they do somewhat.  <P>This comparison does not take into account the cleric DD shout which in some cases will tip the scale in favor of the smite cleric.
</FONT>
