<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
Well I read the beginning of this thread and got some ideas I wanted to get down before I read the rest and forget, so if I am repeating someone else I apologize.<P>RvR is the idea behind this game.  However, many casting classes must act differently during RvR than during regular combat.  This makes absolutely no sence at all.  Magicians in the days of Camelot were POWERFUL, thats why we remember all the names of people so well.  Everyone knows Arthur and Lancelot just cause thats who it was all about.  But everyone also knows Merlin and Morgana.  Why?  They were powerful even if thier roles weren't as large.<P>I say, let EVERY caster from EVERY realm be able to use EVERY spell the EXACT same way in RvR as the rest of the game.  If I were on a roleplay server I'd be screaming alot more about this because it just makes no sence.  Everything other classes get works the same everywhere, so why not ours?  Charm out of the question you say?  Who's to say we can't add a disspell spell for other realms or even add the effect to amnesia for ourselves?  As I see it right now, aside from aoe mez and aoe debuffs, which isn't all that great, we are USELESS in RvR because our spells are designed for fighting mobs/rendered useless in RvR.  Why give us spells if we can't use them to do what the game was designed for?<P>------------------------------------------<P>Alright, now have I have finished reading the rest of the thread I have little more to both say and ask about.<P>First off, i3ullseye can you please define broken?  I believe many people would define broken as "unable to do what the class was designed to do."  Also, what exactly were we designed to do?  From the Dark Age of Camelot wed site -<BR>"Sorcerers are spellcasters who specialize in mind control of their enemies. They can even control lesser-intelligence creatures and command them to do their bidding."<BR>Combine this with what is the first boasted concept of the game -<BR>"Realm-based Player vs. Player combat with territorial acquisition and siege warfare."<P>Now put these two together.<P>Sorcerers are spellcasters who specialize in mind control of their enemies. They can even control lesser-intelligence creatures and command them to do their bidding in Realm-based Player vs. Player combat with territorial acquisition and siege warfare.<P>Is this not what our class is supposed to be? Are we not broken as an entire class?<P>As far as it goes, I would love to see every class in the game be able to use all of their abilities exactly the same in RvR as in PvE, even if it means some other class on some other realm can do whatever to me. It would make the game a hell of alot more fun.<P>If you want to talk about us being broken, talk about RvR.<P>~Xiem Frightbearer<BR>Shining Force, Lancelot
</FONT>
